:::summary
*The Chronicles of Narnia* is a series of seven fantasy novels by C.S. Lewis, published between 1950 and 1956, set in the magical world of Narnia — a land of talking animals, mythological creatures, and the great Lion Aslan. Lewis, one of the twentieth century's greatest Christian apologists, designed Narnia as a way for children (and adults) to encounter Christian truth as if for the first time, through the imagination rather than through formal doctrine. The series remains among the most beloved works of children's literature ever written.
:::

